Just for fun. Brad Pitt
Beautiful people are often difficult to “caricaturize” simply because their proportions are perfectly symmetrical and hard to grab on to a feature to push or pull. With Brad, he has a distinctive wide jaw, slightly turned up eyebrows, larger bottom lip and a thick head of hair, so that’s what I paid attention to. 
Hard to believe he’s pushing 60.
 
#bradpitt #caricature #caricatura #caricatureartist #portrait #illustration #illustrator #digitalart #editorialillustration #artistsoninstagram #adobe #photoshop #wacom #portraiture

Big shout out to my professional Caricature peeps!! @caricatureparty @ninjasketch @avetiarts @nolanium@ @iscacaricatures @mike_tofanelli and others.
I often draw digital caricature type work but always from the comfort of my office and usually I’ll spend hours on one subject, and lots of undos in Photoshop. Recently I challenged myself to see what I can do in around 10 minutes (pen to paper) but still doing it off of my monitor (credit to amazing reference from @earthsworld ) 
It was incredibly challenging for me and found an even greater respect for professional caricature artists that do the daily grind outdoors at fairs, boardwalks, trade shows. It’s definitely not as easy as you all make it look!! And you do it live….no pressure right?!!! 
Much respect to you all ❤️👊

Oh the Last pic in this series I was trying fast doodles at around 5 minutes…

Quick loose impression “study” of a skinny Post Malone on the Joe Rogan podcast tonight. Very little detail but still trying to get his mannerisms. Sometimes a caricature doesn’t have to be the traditional big head little body, it’s more about the feel of the character.
